{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-86b5a5a54b4dae9d","input":{"filename":"crm_hygiene_action_report.md","title":"CRM Hygiene Auditor Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# CRM Hygiene Auditor – Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Scope**: Review of recent CRM hygiene findings (duplicate accounts, stale owners, missing lifecycle fields).\n\n## Summary of Findings (Top 3 Records)\n| Rank | Record ID | Title | Owner | Status | Impact | Risk | Opportunity |\n|------|-----------|-------|-------|--------|--------|------|-------------|\n| 1 | 03-A | CRM hygiene auditor priority case | RevOps | urgent | 42,951 | **9** (high) | 6.3 |\n| 2 | 03-C | CRM hygiene auditor blocked follow‑up | RevOps | blocked | 18,633 | **8** (high) | 1.9 |\n| 3 | 03-B | CRM hygiene auditor routine queue item | RevOps | in_review | 9,339 | **1** (low) | 0.9 |\n\n## Prioritized Action Recommendations\n1. **Immediate remediation of duplicate accounts (Record 03‑A)**\n   - **Why**: Highest impact (≈ 43k) and risk score 9. Duplicate records corrupt reporting, inflate pipeline, and impede sales productivity.\n   - **Next steps**:\n     - Export the suspect account set using the duplicate‑matching rule.\n     - Validate merge criteria with sales ops.\n     - Perform bulk merge in a sandbox; obtain stakeholder sign‑off before production.\n   - **Assumptions**: Duplicate‑matching rules are already defined; merge permissions exist.\n\n2. **Resolve blockage on follow‑up (Record 03‑C)**\n   - **Why**: High risk (8) but currently blocked; clearing the dependency unlocks further hygiene work.\n   - **Next steps**:\n     - Identify the cross‑functional dependency (e.g., data‑privacy review or integration lock).\n     - Schedule a brief alignment meeting with the owning team.\n     - Document required approvals and set a concrete deadline.\n   - **Assumptions**: The blockage is procedural, not technical.\n\n3. **Routine clean‑up of stale owners & missing lifecycle fields (Record 03‑B)**\n   - **Why**: Low risk but still contributes to data quality drift.\n   - **Next steps**:\n     - Run a report for owners with > 90 days of inactivity.\n     - Reassign or deactivate accounts as per ownership policy.\n     - Enforce required lifecycle fields via validation rules or automation.\n   - **Assumptions**: Ownership policy exists and can be enforced programmatically.\n\n## Overall Prioritization Guidance\n- **Tier 1**: Actions that address **high‑risk, high‑impact** items (duplicate accounts). Allocate dedicated resources and obtain quick approval.\n- **Tier 2**: Actions that remove **blockers** preventing Tier 1 work. Coordinate with the responsible teams.\n- **Tier 3**: Ongoing **maintenance** (stale owners, missing fields). Schedule as part of regular data‑quality sprints.\n\n## Required Approvals & Safeguards\n- **Merge approval** from Sales Ops before any bulk account merges.\n- **Change‑control ticket** for any automation rule updates.\n- **Audit log** of merges and owner reassignments for compliance.\n\n---\n*Report generated by CRM Hygiene Auditor (agent 03-crm-hygiene-auditor). Evidence includes loaded dossier and analyzed records.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:04:27.895Z"}}
